Dignitaries who attended the inauguration of the new Anambra State Governor, Professor Charles Soludo on Thursday were shocked when the wife of the former governor Mrs Ebelechukwu Obiano engaged in a fight with Ambassador Bianca Ojukwu. Mrs Ojukwu is the wife of Late Chief Emeka Ojukwu, the eternal leader of the All Progressives Grand Alliance, APGA. It was gathered that the fight began when Mrs Obiano approached Mrs Ojukwu at the front row where she was seated close to the former governor, Chief Willie Obiano. The reason for the fight which is currently generating reactions on social media is still unknown. However, it was gathered that Mrs Obiano, prior to the fight, was angered by other activities at the event. See video of the fight below: